OL,3,C'I'm in fear for my family's life'
OL,5,F"It's over because I nicked him for a
OL,6,Fphone and until I drop that he said
OL,7,Fthey're staying there and they're just
OL,8,Fgoing to constantly be around my
OL,9,Fhouse. I'm in fear for my family's
OL,10,Flife, that's all."
OL,12,FMr Scott spoke calmly to the operator
OL,13,Fas she asked him if he had noticed
OL,14,Fanyone outside his home in the days
OL,15,Fprior to the threat, but he said he
OL,16,Fhadn't. He further explained that the
OL,17,Fthreats came as a result of an iPhone
OL,18,F"incriminating" Morgan.
